Warintapani (Aymara, possibly composed of wari vicu単a, tapa nest, -n, -ni suffixes, "the one with a nest of a vicu単a", Hispanicized names Huarintapa単a, Huarintapani, Hurintapa単a) is a  mountain in the Andes of southern Peru. It is situated in the Moquegua Region, Mariscal Nieto Province, Carumas District, and in the Tacna Region, Candarave Province, Candarave District.
